# Git Workflow

## Purpose

Maintain clean history that humans and AI can trace across sprints.

## When It Applies

Every commit, branch, and pull request.

## Requirements

- Branch naming: `sprint-N/feature-name` or `fix/short-description`.
- Commits: imperative mood, focus on **why** not what.
- One logical change per commit; no drive-by refactors.
- Never force-push to `main`; never skip hooks unless explicitly requested.
- Update `docs/TASKS.md` when starting/finishing work.
- Record architecture decisions in `docs/DECISIONS.md` (ADR format).

## Examples

```
feat(ui): add ThemeToggle to app shell

Sprint 1 — exposes light/dark/system switching via @repo/ui.

fix(core): make DATABASE_URL optional until adapter is connected

Allows build without .env during Sprint 2-1.
```

## Bad Examples

```
update files
fix stuff
WIP
feat: everything (500 files changed)
```
